lines.text: Damnit McNulty! Next time someone hands you an exploding ham, I'm gonna pass the mustard!
It's me. I'm your husband.
Jack! The only man I ever had sex with.
[passes out]
It wasn't that bad!
Lena! Don't jump to conclusions!
You're the one who's doing an awful lot of jumping, Jack!
Jack, the 20th century must be getting to you.
You have no idea!

[holding Lena prisoner]
We don't hold anyone against their will here at Greenworld, Mrs. Deth.

[sarcasm]
Oh really, well I'll just call a cab then, if you don't mind.
[last lines]
It's a nice house. Glad they could afford it. What did you say he does for a living?
Him? Fortune teller. Yes, sir, real life fortune teller!
You don't know what it was like the last time, waking up in the body of a 9-year-old girl!
Look, we're sending you back to 1991. Your ancestor will be 15 now!
And that's supposed to make me feel better? Guys are going to try to get in my pants!
While you're a girl, McNulty, why not try and act like a lady?
Don't worry, ladies. They're biodegradable!

[to Hap]
You know the council's going out of their way to keep you alive so you can procreate!
You killed him!
Wizards don't die they just be become metaphysically challenged.
